definition: enough (sufficient)/enough (too much)/(coll.) (before adj.) really/(coll.) to reach by stretching out
to touch/to come in contact with/to feel/to be affected by/to catch fire/to burn/(coll.) to fall asleep/(after a verb) hitting the mark/succeeding in
aspect particle indicating action in progress

sentences.english: She put the medicine on the top shelf beyond the reach of her son .
sentences.chinese: 她把药放在了儿子够不着的最上面的架子上。

sentences.english: Mom, would you hang this towel on the rack for me, please. I can't reach it.
sentences.chinese: 老妈，请帮我把毛巾挂到架上，好吗？我够不着。

sentences.english: If your children can't reach the sink on their own, keep a stepstool handy.
sentences.chinese: 如果你的孩子自己够不着洗手盆，就进放一张踏步凳。

sentences.english: Keep her food out of reach when you're not home.
sentences.chinese: 当你不在家的时候，使她的食物在够不着的地方。

sentences.english: He ran over to get it but was unable to reach it.
sentences.chinese: 他跑过去抓住那枫叶，可是够不着。

sentences.english: Tall as she was she couldn't reach the oranges.
sentences.chinese: 她虽然长得这么高，仍够不着那些橙子。

sentences.english: The players found the basket too high to reach.
sentences.chinese: 球员发现篮子太高，够不着。

sentences.english: Portable extinguishers in hold No. 2 not accessible.
sentences.chinese: 放在2舱的手提式灭火器够不着。

sentences.english: Once the koala is dinging to the dog's underside, the dog can't get at it with its jaws.
sentences.chinese: 树熊一旦挂在野狗的下方，野狗的嘴就够不着它了。

sentences.english: Please lift the wooden box down from the shelf for me, I can't reach.
sentences.chinese: 请帮我把木箱子从架子上搬下来，我够不着。

sentences.english: I stretched out a stick to fight with cicadas, can still out of reach.
sentences.chinese: 我把棍子向那只蝉伸去，可还是够不着。

sentences.english: I'm not tall enough to reach the basket.
sentences.chinese: 我不够高，够不着篮球架。

sentences.english: Please lift the box down from the shelf for me, I can't reach.
sentences.chinese: 请帮我把箱子从架子上搬下来，我够不着。

sentences.english: She put the medicine on the highest sheft which her son cannot reach.
sentences.chinese: 她把药放在了儿子够不着的最上面的架子上。

sentences.english: Hydrants sin top deck not accessible.
sentences.chinese: 顶甲板的消防栓够不着。

sentences.english: I cannot reach the apples on the top branch.
sentences.chinese: 我够不着最上边树枝上的苹果。

definition: to be unable to carry/lift (sth heavy)
armpit/also pr. [ge1 zhi5 wo1]/also written 夾肢窩|夹肢窝[ga1 zhi5 wo1]
to jam/to choke/to clutch/also pr. [qia3 zhu4]
to move (sth) aside/to step aside/to move over (when sitting on a bench)/to shift (one's gaze)
there is nothing to be done/one can't do anything about it
erhua variant of 使勁|使劲[shi3 jin4]
to crawl/to climb/to get up or sit up
to stay out of (hot water, trouble, awkward situation etc)/to avoid (sb)
